      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To achieve a 0% stockout rate, we need to consider both the average weekly demand (mean) and the variability represented by the standard deviation. Assuming a 95% service level (to minimize stockouts) with z-scores of 1.65, here are the calculations:\n\nSKU_A:\n- Reorder Point = (Avg demand per week) + (z-score * std dev)\n- Reorder Point = 50 + (1.65 * 10) = 66.5 units (approx. 67 units)\n\nSKB:\n- Reorder Point = 200 + (1.65 * 45) = 296.25 units (approx. 296 units)\n\nSKU_C:\n- Reorder Point = 10 + (1.65 * 5) = 18.25 units (approx. 18 units)\n\nTo maintain a 0% stockout rate, keep weekly safety stock equivalent to the standard deviation multiplied by the desired service level z-score:\n\n- Safety Stock for SKU_A = 1.65 * 10 = 16.5 units\n- Safety Stock for SKU_B = 1.65 * 45 = 74.25 units\n- Safety Stock for SKU_C",
