      "content": "To achieve a 0% stockout rate, you would theoretically need to calculate safety stock and reorder points that account for any possible fluctuation in demand. However, maintaining precise levels is impractical due to continuous changes in lead times, demand, and many other variables which we cannot predict.\n\nBut for purposes of these calculations, though this method would guarantee a negligible stockout rate, we resort to using higher service level calculations which can effectively approximate a 0% stockout rate.\n\nAssuming a stricter service level, say 99.999%, which corresponds to a z-score of approximately 4.05, here's the updated calculation:\n\nSKU_A:\n- Reorder Point = 50 + (4.05 * 10) = 90.5 units (approx. 91 units)\n- Safety Stock = 4.05 * 10 = 40.5 units\n\nSKU_B:\n- Reorder Point = 200 + (4.05 * 45) = 422.25 units (approx. 422 units)\n- Safety Stock = 4.05 * 45 = 182.25 units\n\nSKU_C:\n- Reorder Point = 10 + (4.05 * 5) = 30",
